A lightweight command-line tool written in Go that pulls RSS feeds from multiple sources, 
stores them in PostgreSQL, and lets you browse aggregated posts.

Requirements: Go and Postgres 

go install github.com/Old-Goggles/blog_aggregator@latest

Configuration
Create a file named .gatorconfig.json in your home directory.
macOS/Linux: ~/.gatorconfig.json
Windows: $HOME.gatorconfig.json

Example:
{
"db_url": "postgres://USERNAME:PASSWORD@localhost:5432/DBNAME?sslmode=disable"
}

Available Commands

gator register <name>
gator login <name>
gator users
gator addfeed <name> <url>
gator feeds
gator follow <url>
gator unfollow <url>
gator agg 30s
gator browse [limit]

